[{"id":"FT542956","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<p>The four pictures present a story. Imagine you are writing the story to a friend. Narrate a complete story as suggested by the pictures. Give your story a beginning, a middle, and an end. Type your response in the target language.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Four pictures are shown in a square grid to present a story.   Picture 1 is in the upper left corner. Three people are sitting around a table with plates and bowls of food. The black man on the left is pouring tea, the white man at the end of the table is eating with chopsticks, and the asian woman on the right is adjusting the napkin on her lap.   Picture 2 is in the upper right corner. The plates of food on the table are empty waiter is presenting the check to the three diners. The black man is holding open his empty wallet, the white man is pulling his empty pants pockets inside out, and the woman is holding a few coins in her hand.  Picture 3 is in the lower left corner. The woman is holding a cell phone and pressing buttons. A thought bubble above her shows an old man with white hair and glasses. There is a dollar sign next to his face.   Picture 4 is in the lower right corner. The woman and two men who were eating at the table are standing behind the older man as he hands a credit card to a woman at a cash register.\" height=\"349\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/6ee256bf37f2051bd97ce745f1fc24b1/original.jpg\" width=\"355\" /></p>\n","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"You will be asked to write in Chinese in a variety of ways. In each case, you will be asked to write for a specific purpose and to a specific person. You should write in as complete and as culturally appropriate a manner as possible, taking into account the purpose and the person described."}]}]